1. Endpoint Hardening & Custom File Integrity Monitoring (FIM)
Out-of-the-box SIEM implementations lack granularity for unique enterprise directories. To address this, the default Wazuh syscheck architecture was manually tuned.
Configuration: Modified the native ossec.conf file via elevated administrative privileges to implement a real-time tracking mechanism on non-standard staging paths.
Scope Expansion: Monitored system configuration elements alongside user-accessible directories (C:\test) to audit active user operations.
Validation: Verified the distinction between asset "Inventory snapshots" and live cryptographic "Event journals" by modifying local test assets and tracking rule state variations.
2. Telemetry Optimization (Microsoft Sysmon Integration)
Standard Windows Security Event Logs are historically blind to process line heritage. To capture volatile endpoint execution patterns:
Deployed Microsoft Sysmon (System Monitor) using the community-vetted SwiftOnSecurity configuration baseline.
Configured the Windows Wazuh Agent to ingest and parse the raw Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon/Operational event channel channel using an explicit eventchannel log format wrapper.
